Author: bogybogy#3962
Content: the way ETH is designed - a higher ETH price makes no sense for users when it comes to economics and competition.  There is a big discrepance between user needs and speculator interests. Or am i wrong?

Author: bogybogy#3962
Content: This is the way I see it: The largest network wins. That network will swallow users from other competing platforms because users by default (human nature?) migrate towards the most popular platform. This doesn't swallow all the value from others just the majority.

Author: bogybogy#3962
Content: Therefore the largest most popular money networks maintain the most users and therefore power and influence. Today this is still the US dollar. This is quickly changing however.

Author: actionslacks#4072
Content: as crypto usage grows, and more money flows in, the most effecient and secure protocols will gain the most value. because time IS money. And attacks will become more serious and pervasive. small projects witn low hashrates and little security will be attacked mercilessly. popularity is important for getting eyes on the project now, and bringing investors in. but this whole show is just getting started.                  we're still in act 1. act 2 will likely bring more serious govt attempts to control this phenomenon. steering clear of their purview and jurisdictions seems like a smartest way to proceed right now, as opposed to spending millions of dollars and months/years on compliance.

Author: bogybogy#3962
Content: Bitcoins dominance in the market will not change if the rules of the game aren't changed. It is my personal belief that there is a chance that central governments will begin heavily monitoring the Bitcoin network making it unpleasant to use by your average Joe. Remember that Bitcoin is only pseudo anonymous and if they can tie you to a public address somehow they will. If laws around crypto currency aren't significantly changed for the better and you haven't paid capital gains in certain nation's like the U.S. they will make life very difficult for you. At this point Bitcoin will lose a portion of one of its most important properties. Censorship resistance. No central power or authority seeks to limit it's own power. It only seeks to ever increase it. This is the collective human nature that manifests itself in central governing bodies. This all stems from greed and there is nothing that will stop that. With all of that said. If we are talking network effects and what I believe will win long term as true hard money it has to be a privacy coin. Specifically a privacy coin whose network can scale very well.
